# Canonical citation metadata. GitHub reads this file to render the
# "Cite this repository" button.
#
# Authorship note: the citable author is the human director (Randy Crespo), with
# Dandelion Engineering as the affiliation/organization. AI tools are not listed
# as formal authors under current citation norms (they cannot take responsibility
# for the work), so the AI collaboration is disclosed in `abstract` instead. This
# is deliberate and matches Dandelion Engineering's transparency standard.
#
# License scope is intentionally NOT declared here: this work is path-scoped
# (MIT for code, CC BY 4.0 for prose, datasets under their source licenses), and
# CFF treats multiple `license:` values as "either/or," which would misstate that
# split. `LICENSING.md` is the authoritative license-scope record.
#
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Robot Structural Proprioception"
# Set to `dataset` if the primary released output is data rather than software.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Crespo
    given-names: Randy
    affiliation: Dandelion Engineering
abstract: >-
  An in-progress simulation study asking whether distributed, physically grounded
  structural measurements help a robot recognize and compensate for changes in
  its body or sensors beyond a conventional sensor suite. This work was directed
  by Randy Crespo (Dandelion Engineering) and produced in collaboration with the
  AI research agents Claude (Anthropic) and Codex (OpenAI); the AI contribution is
  disclosed here per Dandelion Engineering's transparency standard.
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-07-16"
url: "https://github.com/Dandelion-Engineering/Robot-Structural-Proprioception"
